# ECP5 LPF — auto-pin assignment for synthesis validation
#
# This file constrains ONLY the clock frequency.  All port-to-pin assignments
# are left to nextpnr (use --lpf-allow-unconstrained).  This is intentional:
# the design has more interface ports than a single physical package exposes
# (the Kami-generated mkModule1 exports full register bus, mu-tensor bus, etc.)
# A production deployment would add a wrapper reducing external ports to
# CLK/RST/UART/LEDs before pin-assigning to a specific board.
#
# This file is for synthesis + P&R validation only (confirms timing closure,
# logic utilisation, routing congestion).

FREQUENCY NET "CLK" 25 MHz;
